I"m<h1 id="raspberry-pi-mouse">Raspberry Pi Mouse</h1>

<p>Raspberry Pi Mouse is a wheel-type robot equipped with a minimal computer Raspberry Pi for programming learning.
This robot complies with the rules of the micro-mice and can compete in the tournament.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/img/robots/raspberrypimouse/RaspberryPiMouse_image.png" alt="RaspberryPiMouse_image" /></p>

<h2 id="features">Features</h2>

<ul>
  <li>You can take advantage of your Raspberry Pi (3b, 2b, B +).</li>
  <li>It supports a variety of programming languages, including Python, C++, and Java.</li>
  <li>Compatible with ROS for robot-controlled middleware
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/ryuichiueda/raspimouse_ros_2">ROS Package</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/rt-net/raspimouse_sim">Gazebo Simlator</a></li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>The source code, including the device driver, is open and distributed on GitHub.
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/rt-net/RaspberryPiMouse_Hardware">Hardware</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/rt-net/RaspberryPiMouse">Device Driver</a></li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

